OL,3,CAssisted dying Bill committee to
OL,4,Cconsider domestic abuse amendment
OL,6,FThe MP behind the assisted dying Bill
OL,7,Fhas insisted she is "committed to
OL,8,Fworking with colleagues" as she
OL,9,Fconfirmed her support for changes
OL,10,Fsuggested by people who voted against
OL,11,Fher proposed legislation in Parliament.
OL,13,FKim Leadbeater said she intends to
OL,14,Fvote for amendments on domestic abuse
OL,15,Fand referral to palliative care as the
OL,16,Fcommittee scrutinising her Terminally
OL,17,FIll Adults (End of Life) Bill sits on
OL,18,FWednesday.
