OL,3,CAssisted dying Bill committee to
OL,4,Cconsider domestic abuse amendment
OL,6,FLabour MP Jess Asato has proposed an
OL,7,Famendment requiring the registered
OL,8,Fmedical practitioner acting as the co-
OL,9,Fordinating doctor to have undertaken
OL,10,Ftraining on domestic abuse, including
OL,11,Fcoercive control and financial abuse.
OL,13,FFellow Labour MP Polly Billington has
OL,14,Falso put forward an amendment
OL,15,Frequiring the doctor who has the first
OL,16,Fdiscussion with a person about
OL,17,Fassisted dying to offer to refer them
OL,18,Fto a specialist in palliative, hospice
OL,19,For other care.
