OL,3,CAssisted dying Bill committee to
OL,4,Cconsider domestic abuse amendment
OL,6,FBoth MPs voted against the Bill at
OL,7,FSecond Reading in November.
OL,9,FMs Leadbeater said she will support
OL,10,Fchanges to her Bill if she believes
OL,11,Fthey will make it stronger.
OL,13,FShe said: "It is the job of this
OL,14,Fcommittee to look at ways in which the
OL,15,FBill can be made stronger and more
OL,16,Fworkable and I have made clear
OL,17,Fthroughout that I will support
OL,18,Famendments that do this.
