OL,3,CAssisted dying Bill committee to
OL,4,Cconsider domestic abuse amendment
OL,6,F"These amendments further strengthen
OL,7,Fthe already robust protections in the
OL,8,FBill, helping to ensure that every
OL,9,Fperson who seeks assisted dying does
OL,10,Fso fully informed of their options and
OL,11,Fprotected from coercion."
OL,13,FOf the amendments, she said: "By
OL,14,Frequiring doctors involved in assisted
OL,15,Fdying assessments to undergo
OL,16,Fspecialist training in recognising
OL,17,Fdomestic abuse and coercive control,
OL,18,Fwe are embedding world-leading
OL,19,Fsafeguarding standards into law.
